Re: bitcoin generation broken in 0.3.8?

Bitcointalk

2010-08-09 18:50:41 UTC - [11]Original Post

   I found that SSE2 only added a slight 2% speedup, which didnʼt seem
   worth the incompatibility.  I was trying to take the safer option.
   It doesnʼt look to me like Crypto++ could be deciding whether to use
   SSE2 at runtime.  Thereʼs one place where it detects SSE2 for deciding
   some block count parameter, but the SSE2 stuff is all #ifdef at compile
   time and I canʼt see how that would switch at runtime.  Maybe Iʼm not
   looking in the right place.
   Should we enable SSE2 in all the makefiles?  It seems like we must in
   case someone compiles with 64-bit.
   I will recompile the 64-bit part of the Linux 0.3.8 release.
